I-Design, Issue 331
------------------------

===> TOPIC: HELP NEEDED WITH COPY PROTECTION

Catherine Parvensky Barwell asked for some help in I-Design that
again, applies to all Internet businesses. Has this happened to you?

-----------------------------

I have been having a problem with people copying one of my websites
(www.grocerybiz.info). In one case, the individual actually stole
the entire 100+ page site, downloaded it into a database and was
prepared to sell replicated sites to others. I have the site right
click protected, but this does not prevent someone from selecting
"save as" from the file menu, nor does it prevent someone from
saving pages from Adobe Acrobat (which has also happened). I have
taken appropriate action against the copyright infringers, but I
would like to prevent this from happening yet again in the future.

Does anyone know how to adequately protect an entire site from being
copied?

Any help would be greatly appreciated.

---------------------------

There's been only one response so far from Kim Krause:

---------------------------

For Catherine, regarding copied websites, I've found this site,
http://www.pirated-sites.com/ , to be interesting. Be sure to check
out their FAQ. Also, I tried to gather a lot of resources into one
place here: http://www.cre8pc.com/scam_protectsite.html

---------------------------

Do you have any suggestions for Catherine?

mailto:report@adventive.com?Subject=CopyProtection


